  "blurb": "A sharply drawn contemporary villa on an elevated Chaweng hillside, stepping down its slope in cantilevered levels toward two infinity pools and an open Gulf of Thailand horizon. Four sea-view suites, a private spa and a gym make it a fully equipped retreat, offered furnished and ready to occupy.",
  "detail": "Cut into a hillside above Chaweng, this villa is a study in clean architectural lines — broad flat roofs, expansive glass facades and terraces that cantilever out over the slope to frame an uninterrupted view of the Gulf. The levels are stacked so that living spaces, bedrooms and pool decks each command the same wide sea outlook, at its most striking at dusk when the coastline lights come on below.\n\nThe heart of the home is an open-plan living and dining area under high ceilings, opening through sliding walls to a sun deck and the first of two infinity-edge pools. A second pool and further lounging terraces step down the hill, giving the property distinct places to swim and gather while keeping the same horizon in view throughout.\n\nFour sea-view bedroom suites are arranged for privacy, each with its own en-suite bathroom and quiet outlook over the water. Wellness and leisure are built in: a private spa and massage room, a sauna and a fully equipped gym sit alongside an outdoor bar and barbecue area for entertaining.\n\nCompleted in 2013 on a freehold, Chanote-titled plot of roughly 2,032 m² and offered fully furnished, the villa lies within easy reach of Chaweng’s beaches, restaurants, marinas and the airport. Its elevated position keeps it private while remaining close to the island’s busiest coast — well suited to a private residence or a high-yield rental.",
